Sekarang ini banyak orang terobsesi dengan perkembangan. Karir harus berkembang. Nilai harus berkembang. Perusahaan harus berkembang dan sebagainya. // Perkembangan mengandaikan perubahan dan perubahan mengandaikan apa yang tadinya hanya kemungkinan bisa menjadi fakta. Artinya untuk berkembang kita harus siap untuk berubah. Kalau kita tidak berubah, maka perkembangan tidak akan pernah terjadi. Banyak orang mau berkembang dalam hidupnya, tetapi mereka tidak bersedia berubah, yakni mengubah cara hidup, cara berpikir, cara merasa, dan mengubah nilai-nilainya. // Memang perubahan itu menyakitkan. Perubahan membuat kita masuk ke dalam ketidakpastian. Nilai-nilai dan pandangan yang kita anut sebelumnya tergoncang. Kita pun jadi gelisah. // Namun perubahan seringkali tidak bisa dihindari. Menolak perubahan pada akhirnya akan merugikan kita sendiri. Satu-satunya cara adalah bersikap terbuka dan berbesar hati menghadapi perubahan. Ingatlah bahwa hidup itu sendiri adalah perubahan. Hidup berubah dan kita ikut berubah di dalamnya. Menolak perubahan berarti menolak hidup itu sendiri. Apakah anda siap untuk menolak kehidupan? #tarot #today

New York- .  I sat there on sheets of leather juxtaposed between pieces of gum kissing my familiar goodbye, They told me, "be safe" as they started to cry, . What they didn't understand was that I was on that "Empire State of Mind" high, Until I saw how many dreams die, . I photographed dead dreams on streets which told history, Which I had been told were colored by democracy . Democracy? Are you fucking kidding me? . Is this what you call the American Dream? Told by that clown whose hair looks like tangerine whip cream . No but seriously, is this closet that I'm in really what I saw on that T.V. Screen, Which preached about all I could possibly be? . How can this be? When all I see is inequality, Disguised by racialized systems of hierarchy . Is this what "Make America Great Again" really means? Eradicating all our dreams squeaky clean? . Dreams of who? Surely not the fortunate few! . Dreams that once could breathe, Much like grandma before she was tied up to that machine . Now she's dying because she has no green, Is this what you call the American dream? Is this really the Land of the Free? Because it seems to me that we are held in captivity behind bars of greed. . Ontem bateu na trave!!!! Mas hoje Deus permitiu que eu fosse o Campeão do Absoluto na Faixa Preta Master 2 no New York Open NoGi (Sem Kimono) Glória a Deus!!!!! Lutei na minha categoria antes e fui vice campeão.  Durante a luta tomei uma cabeçada e fiz um corte acima do olho, estava desanimado para lutar o Absoluto (divisão que lutam todos os pesos juntos sendo classificados apenas os 4 primeiros colocados de cada categoria) alem de ser a categoria mais dificil da competição, eu sabia que com certeza iria enfrentra atletas maiores e bem mais pesados do que eu, mas algo dentro de mim estava me dando força e dizia assim... Vai lutar porque Eu sou contigo!!!!! Meu irmão, quando Deus tem algo para sua vida, você pode até não entender porque as coisas não acontecem do jeito que vc quer, ou como vc imagina, mas os planos de Deus jamais se frustrarão. No final acabou tudo acontecendo bem melhor do que eu imaginava!!!! Obrigado a toda minha equipe Ryan Gracie Team, Familia Maresias Bjj, SerraBjj Team New York, Prefeitura de São Sebastião, Secretaria De Esportes, Koral Fight Co, Clinica Massucato, Açai Kings. Yesterday while I was walking in Upper East Side, Manhattan I lost my wallet. I was so busy with people taking photos of Penelope that I couldn't notice the exactly moment when I lost it. I got really nervous. Inside of my wallet, I have all my credit cards, and here in the USA anybody can use the card. Stores don't ask for a document, signature ou passcode. Also, I had $500 in cash and my American documents. I started to call to the credit card companies to cancel my cards in the middle of the street. At that moment, my phone rang and an unfamiliar number appeared on my screen. It was a policeman saying that somebody had found my wallet and they had dropped at the police office. The place was just one block away from where I was. I got so excited. All my documents, cards and cash where inside of my wallet, untouchable. I was so luck! Thank New York City and People for this service and honesty. 🇧🇷 Ontem enquanto estava andando no Upper East Side, Manhattan perdi minha carteira. Eu estava tão ocupada com pessoas tirando fotos da Penélope que eu não lembrava do momento exato quando eu a perdi. Fiquei muito nervosa. Dentro de minha carteira, eu tinha todos os meus cartões de crédito, e aqui nos EUA qualquer um pode usar o cartão. As lojas não pedem documento, assinatura ou senha. Além disso, eu tinha US $ 500 em dinheiro e meus documentos americanos. Comecei a telefonar para as empresas de cartão de crédito para cancela-los, estava bem na entrada de um metro. Naquele momento, meu telefone tocou e um número desconhecido apareceu na tela. Era um policial dizendo que alguém tinha encontrado minha carteira e eles tinham deixado no escritório da polícia. O lugar era apenas uma quadra de onde estava. Eu fiquei tão animada. Todos os meus documentos, cartões e dinheiro estavam dentro da minha carteira. Eu tive muita sorte! Obrigada New York City por este serviço e honestidade. Uma vez perdi meu iPhone e telefonei para ele e a pessoa que o achou imediatamente me devolveu.

Havalimanına indikten sonra shuttle bus’lar ile en yakın metro istasyonuna ücretsiz ulaşım sağlıyorsunuz. Metroya ulaştıktan sonra ise işiniz çok kolay.klasik bir söylem olarak evet inanılmaz bir metrosu var New-York’un. New-York’un muhakkak görülmesi gereken,simgesel her noktasına metro ile gidebilirsiniz bu sebeple biz hiç hop on hop off bus kullanmadık. Ama özellikle Times Square’de size bu otobüs şirketleri ısrarla tur satmaya çalışacaklar, ve gerçekten çok ısrarcılar kurtulamıyorsunuz. Biz çeşitli bahaneler ile zor kaçtık eğer ki gerçekten ilgilenmiyorsanız sakın bulaşmayın. Bizim otelimiz 5.Caddeye inanılmaz yakındı, ve Central Park’ın tam karşısındaydı. O sebeple 5.Cadde üzerinden ulaşabileceğimiz her noktaya günde ortalama 13 km yürüyerek ulaştık. Şehrin haritasını okumak, ulaşmak istediğiniz noktaları takip etmek şehrin planlanmasını muhteşemliği sebebiyle çok kolay. Blok blok ilerliyorsunuz, her sokakta numaralar gayet kolay okunuyor, yolunuzu bulmak o sebeple çok kolay. İlk günden sistematiği çözdüğünüz anda, New-Yorker gibi güvenle dolaşabilirsiniz sokaklarda. Ekim ayında gittiğimizden bizce yeterince turist olmasına rağmen hiçbir yerde sıra beklemedik, yüksek sezonlarda simgesel yerlere girmek için çok uzun sıralar beklemek gerekebiliyormuş. Bu sebeple eğer ki yüksek sezonda gideceksiniz (haziran-eylül) city pass tarzı, size sıralarda öncelik hakkı veren kartlardan alabilirsiniz. Örneğin biz en çok sırayı Özgürlük heykeline giden vapura binerken bekledik, yarım saati biraz geçti ama yüksek sezonda daha uzun kuyruklar oluyormuş, kesin bilgi. #instatravel #instagood #instafoto #travelling #travelgram #nyc #newyork #newyorkcity #usa #seyahat #seyahatblog #cokgezenlerkulubu #hurriyetseyahat #gezgin #vacation #manhattan

🌟Говорят, что самые случайные встречи - самые неслучайные. В этом я убедилась, когда встретила девочку👸🏼💃🏼, которая в прямом смысле изменила мою жизнь. Повлияла на отношение ко многим вещам и на понимание настоящей дружбы👭💞. Мы познакомились именно в тот момент, когда мне почти не было где жить🏡 в большом чужом городе - Нью Йорке🗽🏙. И благодаря Диане мы провели наши незабываемые 2 месяца вместе, наслаждались американской жизнью🎉. Наши якрие вечеринки🎊, вечные приключения с поездками на Манхэттен🚕🌃, тренировки в спортзале вечерами🏋🏼💪🏼, совместный поход за продуктами🍏🍭, продолжительный громкий смех😄. Это то чувство, когда вещи в нашем гардеробе были одинаковые👠👗, как по стилю, так и по цветовой гамме. То чувство, когда уже устали повторять что мы подруги, и соглашались с тем, что мы сестры👨‍👩‍👧‍👧. Воспоминания о том, когда украли сумку в Атлантик сити🙈 с документами, пока мы фоткались📸, но благодаря нашему позитиву, это не помешало провести весело остаток выходных. Или как я почти опоздала на самолёт✈️ домой, но в глубине души была бы не против еще хотя бы чуть чуть остаться с Дианой.  Зайка🐰, сегодня в День твоего рождения🎁🎈 я хотела бы пожелать тебе, в первую очередь, оставаться такой же жизнерадостной и лучезарной☀️, улыбчивой и позитивной🤗, верной и искренной, нежной и милой!👼🏼 Не терять себя под влиянием кого-либо или чего-либо. Всегда оставаться такой же уникальной и нереально классной!👌🏼👍🏼 Пусть жизнь будет яркой💐 и наполненной незабываемыми моментами, а все мечты пусть обязательно сбудутся!🌟 Love you❗️💞 Happy birthday!!!🎉🎁 #best #friends #forever #birthday #nyc #newyork #memories #happy #moments

#interesting #USA  10 апреля - "Титаник" вышел в первое плавание  10 апреля 1912 года "Титаник" - крупнейший пассажирский лайнер наплаву отправился из Саутгемптона в Англии в первое и последнее плавание до Нью-Йорка в США.  Среди его 2207 пассажиров были как богатейшие люди мира, разместившиеся в первом классе, так и иммигранты, теснившиеся на палубных местах.  Титаник называли одним из самых безопасных кораблей, который когда-либо был построен. Однако на его борту было всего 20 спасательных шлюпок, которых хватало только для половины пассажиров и членов экипажа. Считалось, что корабль был настолько непотопляемым, что спасательные шлюпки понадобились бы только для спасения выживших с других пароходов.  Через 4 дня путешествия в 23:40 в ночь с 14 на 15 апреля "Титатник" столкнулся с айсбергом. Столкновение оказалось фатальным, и корабль медленно затонул через 2 часа 40 минут.  На следующее утро лайнер "Карпатия" спас 712 выживших. Остальные 1495 пассажиров и членов экипажа погибло. 👉 Подписывайся на наш Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/usa5info/  #USA #America #США #штаты #русскиевамерике #америка #виза #шенген#шенгенвиза #иммиграциявсша #работавсша #визавсша #американцы#шенгенсша #трамп #обама #ny #newyork #chicago #trump #LosAngeles #Chicago #Houston #Dallas #Detroit #Seattle #Washington #Boston

After five hours on the road, I arrived at West Point at midnight, so ready to jump into a comfortable bed. My keys were waiting as I was the last guest to arrive, and as I went up to my room, the epic space nerd in me was so surprised and excited. It turns out they gave me the legendary Buzz Aldren's room to stay in! (He was on NASA's first successful trip to the moon accompanied by Neil Armstrong). I took in all the historic memorabilia in the room, including the guestbook on the table with Buzz's name engraved into it. As I flipped through the pages, I noticed that the man himself left a note every time he stayed in the room! I've added one of his entries into this slide show, and traced my fingers over the words so I can brush up against greatness :). As I got into bed, the thought also crossed my mind that I've spent the night in the same bed as a lunar legend and space walker...which is equal parts awkward and awesome- but it's all good as I slept dreaming of the stars last night #hero #lunarlanding 🚀🌗💫 ____________________________________________ #space #hero #nasa #ny #igny #westpoint #military #america #thatsdarling #wanderlust #adventure #kinfolk #igers #igdc #acreativedc #newyork #hudson #architecture #design #interiordesign #history #hero #inspiration #legend #galaxy #moon @nasa #travel #worldtraveler #instagood

It took 3 years to do it and was at that time the largest ship of all, with a length of 269.06 m, 28.19 m long and 53.30 m prop. NEW YORK, NEW YORK, what to eat!!! In no particular order. 1- @bluestonelanecoffee (brunch/breakfast) I love it here, there are a few locations but my favourite one is in the west village, the avo on toast is YUM and their homemade granola with lemon curd is HEAVEN! I ate here nearly every day 🙈  2- @esquinanyc (dinner) I love it here so so much, any time people go to NYC it's one of the first places I tell them to go, you must book it, but it's a secret hidden Mexican with delish margaritas and the most unbelievable melted cheese with honey and pumpkin seeds that I can't think about without drooling, GO!  3@thebutchersdaughter_official (lunch) this place is so yumm vegetarian, with a great vibe and yummy juices 4- @elreynyc OMG I stumbled upon this cute little cafe, while I was waiting for a roof top bar to open (yes I was alone, and yes I love myself) I didn't plan on eating any food, but then the guy beside me got his food and WOW I nearly robbed his plate! This food is AMAZING a must! If you don't go I'll cry! And then go for a drink at the roof top bar down the road @mrpurplenyc  5- @casamonobarjamon a Michelin stared tapas bar... need I say more 🙌🏼💕 6-@untitlednyc (treat) now now now you CAN NOT, go to NYC and not stop here to get a cookie! If you do, I'll cry again, so go, walk in order a cookie to take away, it takes 8mins (so you know it's gonna be good) and walk out take a bite and be the happiest person alive  7@apothekenyc (drinks) hidden cocktail bar in China town, delicious cocktails, amazing atmosphere and unbelievable live music!! My fav night to go here is a Monday/Tuesday!! 8- all my fav coffee spots I'm just going to put all in one @bluebottle @theelk @birchcoffee @stumptowncoffee all Delish!  9- @thenomadhotel GO FOR LUNCH HERE!! it is fancy, it's delicious, you get a whole loaf of warm bread to your table and it's just so nice in every way!! 10- @twohandsnyc (lunch) love it here, they have two places, both Delish!! I have lots of other places I liked but I'm running out of room in this post, so the final thing I need to tell you to do is GO AND SEE @sleepnomorenyc ITS INCREDIBLE!

#TravelTuesday, you know, not only have I enjoyed going wherever & whenever, the Spirit of the God has led me to go, I have met some of the most #BeautifulPeople, along the way! These are photos from a time in my life, where I was mutually embraced & honored, by #Nigerians, as a part of the #AnglicanChurchOfThePentecost.  As you can see from the photos, I was truly #Blessed & #HighlyFavored in their presence. The cloth that you see me wearing was given to me & I was taken to one of their seamstresses, where I chose the style & the way I wanted to wear it. I attended an Inauguration of the Missionary Diocese of the Trinity, where there were hundreds of people from #Nigeria, wearing the same material in hundreds of styles! This was one of the most memorable moments of my spiritual life!  Soon after, I invited the Rev. Paul Aduba to meet my Father, who, as you can see, put on some African clothing he'd had & was given by one of his good friends in #NewYork. When the Rev. saw the quality of the material that my Father is wearing, he was in awe & called my Father a King. Up until that moment, I had no idea how much worth the material we were wearing held, with respect to the country of #Africa & I don't think my Father really did either.  #NeverTheLess, my Father has always treated me as #Royaltly, so much so, one morning, after waking up to the smell of breakfast, my Father was always cooking, jokingly, in my #ComingToAmerica voice I said, "Father, I am over 40, do you think perhaps just once I might cook my own breakfast?" Lol! Even still, whenever I visit home, some things will never change. With that being said, some people always wonder why I would leave a life they long for, while others seem to think the life I've lived is undeserving, for someone like me. Well, hey, my life just comes & goes to show, with whatever territory I'm in, I've learned, I'm worth a lot more!

Discomfort or pain - feeling uncomfortable in our skin or some health scare- can be great motivators to get us started on a fitness journey. They help us to get up early, train, tolerate discomfort,  discipline ourselves and give us momentum to shift our lives toward something that we desire more; health, fitness, strength and feeling empowered.  Even thou fear and pain are great to get us moving, when they keep running the show our lives become full of anxiety, stressed and imbalanced.  This is why I recommend you to switch your motivation onto LOVE .  The difference between the two paths is the experience itself, and we don't just want to lose weight to look good, but we want to feel fulfilled and happy. Our body is a vehicle and an expression of that.  Love your body enough to eat clean...don't just do it to lose weight.  Love your body enough to train and become strong.  Love yourself enough to want to be your best.  Weight loss from love is about gaining balance and healing. Don't let fear cloud your journey.  Knowing how your journey changes by your intention: which one will you choose Love or Fear?  Remember it is a choice you make, choose wisely and consciously!

Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis at a book fair at The Plaza Hotel in New York City on April 1, 1977 ⎯ "She was always reading! That’s the image I have when I think of her. In New York, she’d be reading when I came home from school or in the evenings. In the summer, we’d swim in the mornings, and in the afternoons she’d read on the porch. She always said that reading the memoirs of Versailles was the best preparation she had for the White House, because the way people behaved at court was like how they did around the president. She had a deep engagement with literature, history, plays, and poetry. They gave her strength, even in the difficult times." ~ Caroline Kennedy talking about her mother in an interview with PARADE about Jaqueline Kennedy: Historic Conversations on Life with John F. The Statue of Liberty is a colossal neoclassical sculpture on Liberty Island in New York Harbor in New York City, in the United States. The copper statue, a gift from the people of France 🇫🇷 to the people of the United States 🇺🇸, was designed by French sculptor Frederic Auguste Bartholdi and built by Gustavo Eiffel. The statue was dedicated on October 28, 1886. A empresa TKTS, um dos melhores lugares para se conseguir desconto para os shows, os ingressos chegam até 50% de desconto para shows no mesmo dia. O problema é que raramente se tem ingresso para os shows mais procurados e famosos, pois são só os que estão com ingressos sobrando. Há algumas TKTS espalhadas por Nova York. Como no caso da TKTS da Times Square, o mais conhecido e suas filas, dependendo da época do ano, são gigantescas. Há um pequeno guichê da TKTS perto do Píer 17 em South Street Seaport. Ele fica localizado na esquina entre as ruas Front e a John e é difícil encontrar filas. O melhor horário é ir pela manhã. Outro guichê com filas pequenas é o Downtown Brooklyn (1 Metrotech Center, Brooklyn).#tkts#broadway #teatros #vacation #newyork

Зубчатая линия горизонта, контур футуристических зданий на фоне неба – это Мидтаун-Манхэттен. Средневековый "взлет" шпилей и колоколен. Здесь есть что-то от джунглей и немного от небесного города, который звонит для вас в колокола – однако звук не долетает. Ничего живого, ничего человеческого. Ни машины, ни малейшей ряби на воде. Город-фантом? Нет, ничто не заставит нас усомниться в его чистых контурах, в напряженности их вибрации, в их реальности. Чтобы понять этот город, надо поддаться его чрезмерности. Тысячи лиц. Улицы, глубокие как каньоны, по дну которых течет людской поток. Сразу чувствуешь, что ирреальность Нью-Йорка проистекает от переизбытка реальности. Начинает кружиться голова. Состояние эйфории не покинет вас, даже если бы вы прожили здесь сто лет. Такая легкая форма сумасшествия иногда настигает и нью-йоркцев. Это как опиум. . اینفینیتی از QX80 مونوگراف در نمایشگاه خودروی نیویورک رونمایی کرد . سرانجام #اینفینیتی از نمونه‌ی مفهومی شاسی‌بلند خود رونمایی کرد. هرچند هنوز تصاویری از طراحی داخلی خودرو منتشر نشده است. .  اینفینیتی مونوگراف دقیقاً شبیه به تیزرهای منتشرشده از آن در چند روز گذشته است. این مدل که حالا در #نمایشگاه_خودروی_نیویورک رونمایی شده است، آینده‌ی اینفینیتی در بازار شاسی‌بلندهای فول‌سایز را به نمایش می‌گذارد. .  این طرح مفهومی به رنگ طلایی و با رگه‌های کرومی تزئین شده است. ستون جلویی و مشکی‌رنگ #خودرو شمایل ویژه‌ای به ظاهر مونوگراف داده است و دستگیره‌‌ی درها نیز نمای زیبایی دارند. تایرهای خودرو روی رینگ‌های دورنگ ۲۴ اینچی سوار شده‌اند و طبق ادعای اینفینیتی، ظاهر آن‌ها شبیه به رینگ‌های ۲۶ اینچ است. یکی از به‌روزرسانی‌های قابل پیش‌بینی، قوس زیاد جلوپنجره است که در سایر مدل‌های جدید اینفینیتی نیز دیده می‌شود. این جلوپنجره بلندتر و کشیده‌تر است و با الگوهای توری تزئین شده است. .  اینفینیتی در قسمت جلوی خودرو از چراغ‌های LED شبیه به دکمه‌های #پیانو استفاده کرده است. این طراحی در سایر نمونه‌های کانسپت نیز دیده می‌شود. چراغ‌های جلو تا لبه‌ی کاپوت پیش رفته‌اند و به یک نوار باریک از چراغ‌های رانندگی در روز (Driving Light) ختم شده‌اند. نمای پشتی خودرو نیز با چراغ‌های مشابه اما باریک‌تر، به همراه اگزوزهای کشیده تزئین شده است. یک باله‌ی عقب نیز به‌منظور هدایت بهتر جریان هوا در انتهای بدنه نصب شده است. ستون انتهایی بدنه هم دستخوش تغییر شده است. .  متأسفانه اینفینیتی تصاویری از نمای داخلی خودرو منتشر نکرده، اما گفته است، زمانی که درهای خودرو باز شوند، یک رکاب آلومینیومی به مسافران برای ورود به خودرو کمک خواهد کرد. .  اینفینیتی می‌گوید این نمونه‌ی مفهومی مثالی از چگونگی پیشرفت طراحی بدنه‌ی شاسی‌بلند QX80 در طول زمان است. این مدل مفهومی اولین محصول با نام مونوگراف است که انتظار می‌رود که در سایر طراحی‌های اینفینیتی در آینده نیز به کار گرفته شود. zoomit.ir #car #auto #luxury #newyork #exhibition #cars #tech
